<%= breadcrumbs_for_loan(@loan) %>

<div class="alert alert-block alert-success">
  <h4>Lending Limit Updated</h4>
  <p>This lending limit has been changed to: <strong><%= @loan.lending_limit.name %></strong>.</p>
</div>

<p>If you believe there are now issues with regards to the recalculated De Minimis figure then you <strong>must</strong> cancel the loan.</p>

<p>For example, if the total value of the State Aid for the last three years, including that arising from this application, is now <strong>more than <%= @update_lending_limit.state_aid_threshold.format(no_cents: true) %></strong>.</p>

<p>If there isn't an issue, then please progress as you would do ordinarily.</p>

<div class="table-responsive">
  <table class="table">
    <tr>
      <th>Previous State Aid</th>
      <td><%= @update_lending_limit.previous_state_aid.format %></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>New State Aid</th>
      <td><%= @update_lending_limit.new_state_aid.format %></td>
    </tr>
  </table>
</div>

<div class="form-actions">
  <%= link_to('Offer Scheme Facility', new_loan_offer_path(@loan), class: 'btn btn-primary') if current_user.can_create?(LoanOffer) %>
  <%= link_to('Loan Details', loan_path(@loan), class: 'btn btn-default') %>
</div>